Package fr.univartois.cril.approximation.util.collections.indexed

Class AbstractIndexedCollection<E>

java.lang.Object
java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
fr.univartois.cril.approximation.util.collections.indexed.AbstractIndexedCollection<E>
Type Parameters:
E - The type of the elements in the collection.
All Implemented Interfaces:
IndexedCollection<E>, Iterable<E>, Collection<E>
Direct Known Subclasses:
ArrayIndexedCollection, EmptyIndexedCollection, ListIndexedCollection, RepeatedIndexedCollection, SubIndexedCollection, UnmodifiableIndexedCollection
public abstract class AbstractIndexedCollection<E> extends AbstractCollection<E> implements IndexedCollection<E>
The AbstractIndexedCollection provides a skeletal implementation of the IndexedCollection interface, to minimize the effort required to implement this interface. To implement an unmodifiable collection, only size and get must be implemented. To implement a modifiable collection, the methods add, remove and swap must be overridden.

    • fastClear

      public void fastClear()
      Description copied from interface: IndexedCollection
      Fastly clears the content of this collection. After a call to this method, the collection must look empty. However, this method is not required to actually remove all the contained elements. So, use this method with caution, as it may lead to memory leaks.
